  <summary date="2022-07-06T13:29:38Z" status="Introduced in House">Schools Preventing Hunger in At-Risk Kids Act or the SPARK Act This bill expands automatic eligibility for free school lunches and breakfasts to include children who have been placed in kinship care with a relative or family friend with the involvement of&#160;the state child welfare agency. To enroll in the program, a family must document the child's status to the appropriate local educational agency.</summary>
